06118nam a22008535i 9781501743429DE-B159720220302035458.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220302t20191979nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97815017434297 a10.7591/97815017434292doi  a(DE-B1597)533832  a(OCoLC)1110717056  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 4aPN94 7aPHI0430002bisacsh04a801.952191 aHarari, Josue V., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aTextual Strategies :bPerspectives in Post-Structuralist Criticism /cJosue V. Harari. 1aIthaca, NY : bCornell University Press, c[2019] 4c©1979  a1 online resource (464 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tCritical Factions / Critical Fictions -- tFrom Work to Text -- tThe Supplement of Copula: Philosophy before Linguistics -- tSemiology and Rhetoric -- tWhat Is an Author? -- tThe Text, the World, the Critic -- tMyth and Ritual in Shakespeare: A Midsummer Night's Dream -- tThe Museum's Furnace: Notes toward a Contextual Reading of Bouvard and Pécuchet -- tOn the Interpretation of Ordinary Language: A Parable of Pascal -- tThe Algebra of Literature: The Wolf's Game -- tThe Schizophrenic and Language: Surface and Depth in Lewis Carroll and Antonin Artaud -- tFreud and the Sandman -- tDecentering the Image: The "Project" of "American" Poetics? -- tValéry and the Poetics of Language -- tRoland and the Poetics of Memory -- tGenerating Lautréamont's Text -- tDirections for Further Research -- tContributors -- tBibliography -- tName Index -- tSubject Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aA stellar cast of fifteen contributors seeks to show the direction in which continental and continentally oriented American literary criticism has evolved in recent years. Nine of the essays are published here for the first time; five of the remaining six were translated, by the editor, from the French; only one has previously appeared in English.The essays make available some of the most important and most representative work that has been done in the wake of structuralism. Among the topics treated are the relationships between semiology and literature, anthropology and literature, and psychoanalysis and literature; modern American poetics; algebraic models as epistemological operators; the modes of production of a poem; Flaubert's view of history; and poetic language. Professor Harari has arranged the essays to move from the general to the particular and from the abstract to the concrete. In an informative and ambitious introduction, he discusses each essay in relation to the whole and explains the interrelationships among the various theories and strategies that are represented in the anthology.A book meant for the specialist as well as the novice, for the teacher of literature and criticism as well as the student, Textual Strategies is a brilliant introduction to post-structuralist critical theories and practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCriticism. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Post-Structuralism.2bisacsh1 aBarthes, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeleuze, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerrida, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonato, Eugenio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoucault, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGenette, Gérard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGirard, René, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarari, Josué V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l